[I] Utility to extract UEFI IFR data into human-readable text

[T] UEFI Internal Form Representation (IFR) is a binary format that UEFI Human
[T] Interface Infrastructure (HII) subsystem uses to store strings, forms,
[T] images, animations and other things that eventually supposed to end up on
[T] BIOS Setup screen.

